  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Permanent Handwashing Stations in Uganda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Waterkeeper Alliance is working with Uganda Lake Victoria Waterkeeper and Lake Kyoga Waterkeeper to protect vulnerable communities from the spread of COVID-19 with the installation of permanent handwashing stations needed to prevent the spread of disease. The Waterkeepers will create COVID-19 Task Forces in 40 fishing villages to construct and maintain 80 permanent handwashing stations equipped with soap and water, and provide temperature guns for village health teams to protect 24,300 people.</narrative>
  </description>
